Fold the handmade paper in half and in half again. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a2/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

The fold it diagonally to make a cone shape. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f0/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Trim the widest part of the cone with pinking shears to make the end rounded. Cut off the very end of the pointed part of the cone with scissors. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1d/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1d/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Open the paper out to find a circle with a hole in the middle. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e9/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e9/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut a length of aluminium (aluminum) wire about 30 centimeter (11.8 in) / 12" long. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/96/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Bend it in half and twist the bent end into a circle. This will be your fairy's head. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dc/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dc/Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fairy-for-the-Christmas-Tree-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
